Im a 6 week old newbie to RPGs (just so you know how much "nothing" I know). I am a L9 Saracen Paladin w/specs Slash: 6, Sheild:6, and Chants:10. Here are my Qs:<BR>1)I need to know from a well-seasonned Pally what the very best tactics are in a group. I just got both "Guard" and "Protect" abilities and have no clue as to what the difference is, and how to use them (are they even needed?). <BR>2)I tend to be very focused on the beast in front of me, thus too much distraction (who do I watch out for?) can hinder my effectiveness. <BR>3)I've read about, and tried twisting, but am not exactly sure how that works or if it is more beneficial to my group than just keeping one chant pulsing (and which one?)<BR>4)Best method to solo?<BR>I'd be very grateful for any insights, directions, links to more info anyone could give me.<BR>Thanks! -DiNaan on Guinevere     <IMG SRC="confused.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>"Be audacious and cunning in your plans, firm and persevering in their execution." --Carl von Clausewitz
