<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I am not a pally, but have grouped with a few so in case yhou are still watching this board.<P>1(a).  Guard allows u to block for some one else if you are standing near them.  Get a buddy and Guard for them, if they are shield speced too get them to Guard for you.<P>1(b).  Protect allows you to divert agro created by another character to you.  Put it on the Healer in the group.  Warnikng this may mean that you will get a lot of agro (% .<P>2.  Focus is not a bad thing, but let people know you will be looking in one direction.  If there are more than 1 person tanking then one should be concentrating on the main target and one or more others watching for additional monsters (adds) and one that are going after the casters, particularly the healers.<P>3.  Twisting is changing back and forth between chants, because the pulse time for a chant can be longer than the time to start one up you can get more than one going at a time.  I personally don;t think it's worth it, but if you are soloing of things are really tough it might be.  Armour factor chant is good, Heal Chant does two things, it heals and it generates a lot of agro so you will likely stay the monsters main target, which simplifies things for everyone.<P>4. Solo I can't help with much, except for my personal rule, don;t try to level soloing oranges.  Also try to keep your gear up to spec, try to keep it all yellow.  A blue weapon can really lower your damage output, more than a couple of pieces of blue armour are going to mean you will be taking more damage.  Orange is okay, but will wear out faster and not give you a lot of extra punch, red and purple can be worse than yellow and you are better of saving them for when u are higher level.<P>Hope that was some help.<P>regards, Htzpr23.<P>Kahlil; 21 Minstrel - Bors.
</FONT>
