<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Well met paladin,<P>    I am currently a Paladin of the 41st level and I agree with what the last poster said and might be able to help a little with soloing.<BR>    First off if you can avoid it, dont solo.   The xp when compared to grouping is very low, and it is always dangerous no matter what the con, with the exception of greens and lower cons.  If you are awaiting a group and see mobs (monsters) that are easily solo pulled then give it a shot.  I suggest you have you Aura casted upon yourself and you start out with the Armor chant while you expend your stamina doing styles once your stamina has run out then switch over to the damage chant and you can almost reproduce that same dmg bonuses you were getting on styles.  If the end of the battle seems to be a toss up throw heal chant on and hope that your heals hit before the mob does. If you are in a bad situation and fear you must die, then weave your chants (this is the only time i ever consider weaving).  Dont do oranges for the take too long to kill and your recoop time is far to great, stick to yellows and if you are blazing thru blues or can handle 2 at a time (thus giving a bonus) then try those. But again if it can be avoided dont solo, groups are far better and will usually want you as a good tank.<P>I hope this shines some light on it for you, be wary of your path, that of a Paladin is a difficult road, you will be shunned by some Armsman and some of the more pee-brain clerics will scoff you for taking so much aggro.  If done correctly this is a rewarding class to play.<P>So sayeth Sir Arthearius,<BR>Justicator of the Church<BR>Merlin Server
</FONT>
